5 perception on east side.  Sunny- light wind- algae severe in some areas (east shore) - Easily raked other shores.
Perception of 5 on east shore.  Hazy- hot- water considerably clearer than last check.  Algae tapering off.
Perception of 5 on east shore.  Hazy.  Algae seems to be abating.  Level-1" below benchmark.  Very heavy "septic" smell on east shore.
Perception of 5 on east shore.  Sunny.  Since last report had two reports of strong septic smell- east side.  Confirmed.  What can be done
Perception of 5 on east shore.  Sunny.  Starting to get a weed problem (thought to be wild celery  )
Perception of 5 on east shore. clear- sunny-suspended algae and/or sediment clearly visible.  Lots of violations and little enforcement.
Perception of 4 on east side.  Suspended particles very much in evidence- sunny weather.
Ice off-3/25/90.  Hazy to cloudy.  Severe micro cystis problem last week.  Water smells very bad.  Clarity very bad- worst in history.
Sunny- algae starting to form on bottom.
Hazy- lake is getting worse! help!
Hazy.  Deterioration May be due to several power boats creating huge wakes.  We plan to do a study if funds are available to us and hopefully treat the lake in 1991.
Mostly sunny.  Water cleared considerably.  Lake seems to be cloudy but with less "green algae."
Sunny- green algae starting to form on bottom- not nearly as bad as last and other years.
Hazy.  Reduced visibility- probably due to heavy speed bat use.  Lake far to small for sure a pounding.  Green algae far less than other years.
Sunny.  Appears to be another bloom or turnover.  Lots of rain and heavy boat traffic also hurts.  Lots more weeds than ever- but not as much green algae as in some recent years.
Sunny.  Applying for a study grant.
Sunny- slightly hazy.  Had green scum on water 9/26- no dispersed by breeze.
Ice on eve of 12/25.  There was no secchi reading- just observation.  Happy new year!
Ice out 3/28. Bright and sunny.  Chunks of algae already floating around. Tile-off heavy during past 2 weeks.  Bank erosion May be a problem with high level and power boats.  Silt will be.
Sunny.  Lake is getting cloudy.  Brown instead of green.  Large chunks of algae (or sewage) floating around.  Power boats creating silt problems at shoreline.  Unbelievable-in April!  need no wake!

Slight evidence of suspended particles. sunny- slight haze.  Cannot believe change.  Some evidence of floating or suspended chunks also.  We are very interested in getting into advanced self-help- please advise how.

Clarity unbelievable!  not seen in years.  Sunny- slight haze. still evidence of suspended particles and some chunks of algae.  Some algae forming in spots.  Lots of small dead fish (100s) I think we're ready advanced self help
Sunny.  South wind.  Lots of suspended particles.  Reduced visibility might be due to motor boats and wind.  Algae is really building upon bottom as water warms.
Sunny but hazy.  Suspended particles getting worse and larger.  Algae starting to smell bad.  Lots of dead fish.
Sunny- algae is almost solid 40-50' from shore.  However- it has cleared considerably from 6/2 reading.  Impossible to fish from pier or shore.
Swimming is possible.  Sunny. NE wind has blown algae toward shore.  Weather cool- so few boats.  Water unusually clear.  Some suspended particles.

Sunny and if we didn't rake- it would be 5 algae is 40-50 solid from shore.  Smell is horrible!  however- algae does not seem to be spreading as in other years.  Water is generally clearer than in years.
Algae has been raked from most beaches and appears not to be reforming

Sunny.  Reduced depth probably due to 1.8" rain on 7/22.  Algae does not appear to be reforming.  Abundance of suspended particles.  Of 6 "event" check sites- one on south side had tremendous flow.  Others almost dry
Algae starting to come back.  Appears to be a bloom but could be due to heavy motor boat use.
Hazy sunshine-substantial suspended particles.  Algae returning
Sunny.  Reading taken one day after .8" rain
Algae is "retreating."  what I think is wild celery was a "bumper crop" this year.  It interferes with swimming and fishing.
Hazy sunshine.  Lake has algae particles floating around.  Also chunks of rotting vegetation.  Ice off on 4/8.  This is a far cry from last spring where we had 15'-17' readings.
Sunny. light breeze- brownish algae chunk and suspended particles very prevalent.  Only a few dead small fish.  Lots of silt poured in.  Hurry up "clean water act"
Sunny- hazy.  Lake has cleared considerably- suspended particles quite evident but little algae growth.  Motor boats active since ice out and creating silting during operating hours.
Sunny- algae has really bloomed in last 10 days.  Help! now that Thompson has quitted the clean water bill- how do we stop the drain tiles from polluting out lake   help.
Sunny- slight haze.  Slight improvement in last week in clarity- but algae is thriving.  What about the rye straw treatment- as for lake tides
Sunny.  Water very bad.  Green scum on surface and suspended particles.  Algae buildup has been worse.
Sunny- algae level considerably reduced.  Appears to be dying.  Smell at shoreline is terrible
Sunny- almost flat calm.  Lake has miraculously cleared.  Very little algae.  Wild celery very short.  Probably due to little rain and runoff- more holding tanks and mound systems and cool weather.
Water is cool.  Sunny.  Algae and weed growth appears behind last year
Sunny- slight haze.  Algae and weeds much lower than last year.
Chunks of algae floating all over.  Silt has been pouring in through 2 tiles- site 16e@ for weeks.
The site test 16h2 has finally stopped flowing.
Sunny- suspended particles in water- algae on shoreline
Sunny- slight haze- thick algae growing out 50'- new weed growth
Sunny- best reading this year- suspended algae seems to be declining- much greater weed growth than  1992.
Wild celery very thick- 2 cases of swimmers itch- slight haze- algae very thick- 2 patches of purple loosestrife
Sunny- windy 10-15 mph- algae appears to be dying- water celery taking over- 2 patches of purple loosestrife- 3 cases of swimmers itch
Sunny- algae slowly disappearing- little rain thus no runoff
Sunny- hazy- algae down- wild celery very thick
Sunny- algae receding.  Biggest problem is wild celery- spreading- thick.
Algae starting to bloom-slower because of cold weather.  East side of lake at e3 + e8 is solid algae.
Sunny-east side of lake choked with algae.  Report on 4-25-94 test shows extremely high nitrogen entering through tiles.
Algae not too bad except E side- sites e3 + 8 where it's solid.
Sunny- windy.  Middle of algae bloom.  Algae condition has been worse- have more holding tanks-less faulty systems.  Must stop drain tiles!
Solid green algae not bad-worst at east end drain.  Water clarity worst this year.  Could use more law enforcement!
Sunny-while lake is "cloudy"- lots of suspended particles-algae build-up is less than in past.  With wave action lake really gets dirty.  Need law enforcement for motor boats.
.9" rain on 7/23 p.m.  Sunny- boating extremely heavy creating shoreline turbulence.  Personal water craft especially bad.  Need enforcement!  (something I can't read) .
Sunny- 7/31-2"+ rain-7/31 evening.  Water cloudy- but algae not bad.  Boating pressure heavy.
Sunny.  Less algae- but lots of suspended particles.
Sunny.  Suspended sediment still prevalent.  Daily violations of no-wake laws + encroachment (within 100' of rafts + piers) creating additional sediment.
Public perception due to sediment or dirt.  Heavy rain 2 weeks ago.  Algae dropped way off.  Heavy boating pressure.  Large 1/0 craft.  Shoreline takes a beating.
Clear day- calm- algae close to shore- 20-30 yards.
Cloudy- calm- algae close to shore 20-30 yards.
Some algal blooms- calm water- partly cloudy skies.
Water calm- clear skies- sunny- long string weed growth around the lake.
Clear day.  Some algal bloom present.
30% cloud cover north wind 10mph.  Algae bloom.
